&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Design, implement, scale, and continuously improve Zipline’s legal and compliance programs across Africa, with a focus on sustainable, practical operations that support rapid growth&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Own compliance with U.S. government award requirements, including FARs and 2 CFR 200, and serve as a primary point of contact for U.S. government contracting officers (including at the U.S. Department of State)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead day-to-day compliance workstreams covering sanctions, anti-bribery and anti-corruption, privacy, healthcare, employment, and product-related regulations&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support internal investigations, audits, and risk assessments, partnering closely with People, Finance, and senior leadership&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Manage litigation and disputes across Zipline’s African market&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Translate complex regulatory requirements into clear, actionable guidance fo

